  "poem": {
    "content": "I believe the slush whispers secrets,\nsimilar to cattle lowing in the dawn.\nA sweet ache in my wrist, fragile bone,\nas the artist tries to capture stone.\n\nHe digs in the dirt, a super effort,\nto verify the blast, the earth's retort.\nAn eyebrow arches, a skeptical slant,\nat the process, slow and elephant.\n\nCan beauty rise from such coarse ground?\nA diamond's genesis, profound.\nHe shapes the clay, a fragile hope,\nthat something lovely might elope.\n\nFrom chaos born, a spirit free,\na gentle heart now, meant to be.\nHe must believe, though doubts may tease,\nand find art's truth, to bring him ease.\n\nThe stone remains, a silent guide,\nwhere fragile beauty can reside.",
